The Gauteng Department of Education has learned with shock and disappointment of a break-in at Menzi Primary School in the early hours of yesterday morning. All 185 tablets that the pupils use were stolen. Eight teachersâ€™ laptops, two data projectors, three desk top computers, a plasma TV and petty cash of about R500 was also stolen. The multi-million rand school was recently handed over to the community of Tsakane for the first day of school on Wednesday. Two patrollers were allegedly tied up and locked in one of the store-rooms. A case was opened at Tsakane Police Station.